history.content:
I emailed Professor Levine asking about enrollment policies for this class (didn't notice the "don't email" notice, whoops). Here's his response:

"We'll post instructions for undergrads to apply to enroll in deep RL in late April or early May. Please check the course website over the summer for instructions. Decisions on which undergraduates will be provided enrollment codes will be made in August. Note that this is a graduate class, and we usually have relatively few undergraduate spots. We haven't finalized the prereqs yet, but in past years, CS189 or equivalent was a hard requirement."

children.subject: I opened the website but I don’t see the form anymore... Is the selection already made?
The form for undergrads is up now on http://rail.eecs.berkeley.edu/deeprlcourse/
Also, have any undergrads who filled out the form received some kind of indication that they will be allowed into the course (other than an invite to the Piazza)?

Is it safe to assume they will email undergrads who were selected with a permission code? I'm guessing I didn't make it; I filled out the google form when it first became available. Today I received an invite to the Piazza for the course but no other indication that I will be able to enroll. Asking here because I don't want to bother the instructors unnecessarily with enrollment questions.

history.content: I'm an undergrad student trying to take CS294-112 (Deep Reinforcement Learning) next semester. I noticed on last year's website that they use a Google form for application into this course. It also says don't email the instructor for enrollment questions. So does anyone here know if I need to get on the waitlist before getting the link for the application and filling it out?
history.subject: CS294-112 undergrad need to waitlist first before enrollment?
